% if: executable(brightnessctl)

Brightness Control

The [prgm]brightnessctl[/prgm] command controls screen, and keyboard, backlight brightness.

$ [prgm]brightnessctl[/prgm]                # Show current brightness
$ [prgm]brightnessctl set[/prgm] [arg-value]50%[/arg-value]        # Set to 50%
$ [prgm]brightnessctl set[/prgm] [arg-value]+10%[/arg-value]       # Increase by 10%

Devices:

$ [prgm]brightnessctl[/prgm] [arg]--list[/arg]                    # List all controllable devices
$ [prgm]brightnessctl[/prgm] [arg]-d[/arg] [arg-value]kbd_backlight[/arg-value] [prgm]set[/prgm] [arg-value]50%[/arg-value]  # Control keyboard backlight

[dim]Brightness changes are immediate and don't require sudo (udev rules handle permissions).[/dim]
